# Native macOS Desktop App Techniques

## CSS Techniques

**App Region Control:**
```css
.drag {
    -webkit-app-region: drag;
}

.no-drag {
    -webkit-app-region: no-drag;
}
```
"Users expect to be able to drag the entire window by pressing on the empty space" in custom titlebars.

**Cursor & Selection:**
```css
*, a, button {
    cursor: default;
    user-select: none;
}
```
Native macOS apps display default cursors on interactive elements, reserving pointer cursors only for external links.

## Font Sizing

- Standard system font size: 13px (though 14px works well as compromise)
- Use `rem` units for scalability
- System font stack:
```css
html {
    font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont;
    font-size: 14px;
}
```

## Focus/Blur State Management

Monitor window focus events in main process:
```javascript
window.on('focus', () => window.webContents.send('focus'));
window.on('blur', () => window.webContents.send('blur'));
```

Listen in renderer process and "replace colors with shades of gray" when unfocused to indicate inactive state.

## Additional Native Patterns

- Window position/size restoration between sessions
- Preferences window with keyboard shortcut (⌘,)
- Standard menu bar with keyboard shortcuts
- Undo/redo functionality
- Offline support with background syncing
- Dark mode with matching window background colors (preventing white flashes during resize)

